  "text": "In this paper, we address the aforementioned issue by proposing to learn user profiles and product review information separately before making a joint prediction on sentiment classification. In the proposed Dual User and Product Memory Network (DUPMN) model, we first build a hierarchical LSTM [CITATION_1] model to generate document representations. Then a user memory network (UMN) and a product memory network (PMN) are separately built based on document representation of user comments and product reviews. Finally, sentiment prediction is learned from a dual model.",
